    <item>
      <title>Maintenance Log - Eleventh Week: Assets, Logs, Filtering, and Creating Maintenance Entries</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/Portfolio/devlog/maintenancelog-eleventhweek/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 12 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>cph-ja472@stud.ek.dk (Jesper Andersen)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/Portfolio/devlog/maintenancelog-eleventhweek/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Devlog Week 11: Assets, Logs, Filtering, and Creating Maintenance Entries&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;devlog-week-11-assets-logs-filtering-and-creating-maintenance-entries&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#devlog-week-11-assets-logs-filtering-and-creating-maintenance-entries&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This entry focuses on the asset/log workflow: fetching real data from the API, filtering lists, displaying asset details, and adding log creation behind role checks.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;What Changed&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;what-changed&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#what-changed&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;AssetList&lt;/code&gt; now fetches from the real backend API&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Active/inactive filtering implemented via a reusable &lt;code&gt;Select&lt;/code&gt; component&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;AssetDetail&lt;/code&gt; fetches asset + logs in parallel using &lt;code&gt;Promise.all&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Status and task type filters wired to server-side filtering&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&amp;ldquo;Create log&amp;rdquo; is role-gated (TECHNICIAN+) and also hidden for inactive assets&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;CreateLog&lt;/code&gt; includes client-side validation and prevents double-submit&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;CSS Modules adopted for scoped styling&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Asset List: Fetch + Filter Pattern&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;asset-list-fetch--filter-pattern&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#asset-list-fetch--filter-pattern&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;AssetList&lt;/code&gt; implements a reusable pattern used elsewhere in the frontend:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
